{"title":"In the Drops: SunGod Tokas sunglasses, The Road Book 1989, SiS protein bars and Tour de France Femmes","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/sungod-tokas-sunglasses","date":1689939236000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/sungod-tokas-sunglasses\">In the Drops: SunGod Tokas sunglasses, The Road Book 1989, SiS protein bars and Tour de France Femmes</a></p>\n\n<p>Welcome back to another edition of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/in-the-drops\" target=\"_blank\">In the Drops</a>. It’s been a busy week in cycling, with the Tour de France hurtling towards its conclusion and excitement building for the upcoming Tour de France Femmes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get you ready for the women’s race, we’ve got a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\" target=\"_blank\">full guide</a> to the race, a rundown of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-favourites\" target=\"_blank\">the favourites</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-tour-de-france-femmes\" target=\"_blank\">how to watch</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-tour-de-france-femmes-free-gcn\" target=\"_blank\">free GCN+ passes</a> and a profile of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\" target=\"_blank\">Elisa Longo Borghini</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s not the only racing starting on Sunday though. Emma has lovingly prepared a full guide to <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/transcontinental-race-route-how-to-watch-winners\" target=\"_blank\">the Transcontinental Race</a> and interviewed last year’s winner <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/christoph-strasser-tcr-cyclist\" target=\"_blank\">Christoph Strasser</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In tech news, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/orbea-orca-2024\" target=\"_blank\">Orbea’s new Orca</a> is 6.7kg and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/syncros-capital-sl-wheels\" target=\"_blank\">Syncros’ new aero wheels</a> have their carbon spokes moulded into the rim. Plus, should you need it, James has you covered on all things <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-breathe-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">breathing while cycling</a>. Think it’s easy? Think again. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally we’ve had reviews of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/limar-air-stratos-mips-review\" target=\"_blank\">Limar Air Stratos</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/lazer-vento-kineticore-review\" target=\"_blank\">Lazer Vento KinetiCore</a> helmets as well as the lovely new <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/colnago-c68-road-review\" target=\"_blank\">Colnago C68 Road</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"347\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-970x347.jpg\" alt=\"Subscribe to Cyclist Magazine\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-970x347.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-300x107.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-768x275.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-1536x550.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-750x269.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4-1140x408.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/clickable-subs-promo4.jpg 1818w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<h2>SunGod Tokas sunglasses</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-970x728.jpg\" alt=\"sunglasses on a table\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-970x728.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-300x225.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-768x576.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-750x563.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5-1140x855.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops5.jpg 2048w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The weather has been absolutely scorching recently, although not as bad here in the UK, fortunately, as elsewhere in Europe. Sure, I load up on the suncream, but I’m also partial to picking up a pair of cute looking sunnies at the shop. Not ideal, given the limited UV protection some provide.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These Tokas Sunglasses from SunGod are the lightest pair of sunglasses I own at just 25g and provide 100% UV protection. I chose a black frame and shades to match everything I own, but SunGod offers a variety of combinations including blue and gold if you want to go all out. The frames are 100% recycled too, which I love.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While some SunGod sunglasses are built for exercising, these form part of the company’s Lifestyle Series collection, designed for use off the bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy the Tokas sunglasses now from <a href=\"https://www.sungod.co/en-gb/shop/sunglasses/tokas\" target=\"_blank\">SunGod (from £70)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Road Book 1989 by Cycling Almanack</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-970x728.png\" alt=\"blue book on wood\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-970x728.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-300x225.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-768x576.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-750x563.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2-1140x855.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/robyninthedrops-4.2.png 1893w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Given the scope of results packed into the 12 months of 1989, from Greg LeMond’s 8-second Tour de France victory and his World Championship title to Edwig Van Hooydonck’s first Tour of Flanders success and Lauent Fignon’s second Milan-San Remo win, perhaps it comes as no surprise that it is the first year chosen for The Road Book’s ‘Blue Book’ series, edited by Matt Rendell. Where the red Road Books, launched in 2018, serve as a yearly almanac covering the previous year’s cycling season, the Blue Books are focussed on the history of the sport.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As someone who loves both cycling and history, any chance I get to combine the two is a bonus for me. The book is packed with contributions from star riders including Sean Kelly and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/pippa-york\" target=\"_blank\">Pippa York</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy The Road Book 1989 from <a href=\"https://theroadbook.co.uk/products/the-road-book-1989?variant=44989210984752&amp;currency=GBP&amp;utm_medium=product_sync&amp;utm_source=google&amp;utm_content=sag_organic&amp;utm_campaign=sag_organic&amp;srsltid=ASuE1wR3xBJC5Kh9atQdi4EUT8jOZzIqyL8ndBR2qZcYa68fhWwQF4iwlxQ\" target=\"_blank\">The Road Book (£40)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Science in Sport (SiS) protein bars</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"823\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-970x823.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-970x823.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-300x254.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-768x651.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-1536x1303.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-750x636.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23-1140x967.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-23.jpg 1872w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I’ve never been one to reach for the dark chocolate. But pair it with raspberry? My interest is piqued. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>These new Protein Bars from Science in Sport (SiS) deliver 20g of protein in a variety of tasty flavours. SiS says the Protein Bar is best eaten 30 minutes post-exercise in order to contribute most effectively to muscle mass growth and maintenance, so keep that in mind before you sit down.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re an athlete, all SiS products are Informed Sport Certified – meaning every batch is tested for any banned substances, which is something I find really interesting. Now if you’ll excuse me, it’s been 29 minutes since I exercised. I swear.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy Dark Chocolate and Raspberry Protein Bar (12 pack) from <a href=\"https://www.scienceinsport.com/shop-by-need/recovery/protein-bars/sis-protein-bar-dark-chocolate-raspberry\" target=\"_blank\">Science in Sport (£32.99)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-tour-de-france-femmes-free-gcn\">Watch the Tour de France Femmes with a free GCN+ pass from Lifeplus-Wahoo</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-favourites\">Who are the favourites for the 2023 Tour de France Femmes?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-tour-de-france-femmes\">How to watch the Tour de France Femmes 2023</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">Tour de France Femmes 2023: Everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: Tour de France Femmes build-up</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-970x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-970x970.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-768x768.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-2048x2048.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-75x75.jpg 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-350x350.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-750x750.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/MicrosoftTeams-image-24-1140x1140.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>I. Am. So. Excited. For. The. Tour. De. France. Femmes. Oh, and so is Ozzy, who is the most adorable model you will find. Will Demi Vollering overthrow Annemiek van Vleuten or will someone else spoil the party? Will Marianne Vos win yet another stage? Will Cecilie Uttrup Ludwig give her most entertaining post-race interview yet? The possibilities are endless.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What a moment it is for women’s cycling as we approach the second Tour de France Femmes. Long may it continue. I won’t be there this year (I already have FOMO) but will be posting stage recaps on TikTok. Enjoy the race!</p>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature</strong></em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>You’ve watched the Tour de France…….now ride it in 2024!</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-970x648.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-970x648.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-300x201.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-768x513.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-1536x1027.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-2048x1369.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-750x501.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-1140x762.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Have you got what it takes to ride one of the world’s most gruelling and iconic cycling challenges?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Tour 21 – in partnership with Flutter</strong> and <strong>The Route</strong> see teams of amateur cyclists take on the world’s most gruelling cycling challenges by riding the full Tour de France and Tour de France Femmes avec Zwift routes, one week ahead of the professionals in June and July 2024 to raise funds for national blood cancer, Cure Leukaemia.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Included in the price: accommodation in the official Tour de France hotels, official training and event kit from Official Tour de France kit supplier Santini, all meals and nutritional provision, rolling road closures, dedicated team physios and mechanics and MUCH MORE.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"184\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-970x184.jpg\" alt=\"Tour21 and The Route details\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-970x184.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-300x57.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-768x146.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-1536x292.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-750x143.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-1140x217.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21.jpg 1788w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<div>\n<div><a href=\"https://www.thetour21.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register your interest in riding the Tour de France</strong></a></div>\n\n\n\n<div><a href=\"https://theroute.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register your interest in riding the Tour de France Femmes</strong></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature ends</strong></em></p>\n</div></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/sungod-tokas-sunglasses\">In the Drops: SunGod Tokas sunglasses, The Road Book 1989, SiS protein bars and Tour de France Femmes</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"85a6b0ba887ff291284682a5fad3253a3fa95e864840ab8062f14c3564ca20e3","category":"Cycling"}